  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Rich Captions</h2>
    <p>Captions can contain inline elements like <code>&lt;small&gt;</code> for secondary information such as data sources or date ranges.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Caption with secondary description">{{ richCaptionCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Alternative: <code>aria-labelledby</code></h2>
    <p>When a visible heading immediately precedes the table and serves as its label, you can use <code>aria-labelledby</code> instead of duplicating the text in a caption.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Table labelled by a heading">{{ ariaLabelledbyCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Reference</h2>
    <p>The styles Vanilla Breeze applies to caption elements.</p>
    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="Caption CSS styles">{{ cssReferenceCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Property</th>
          <th scope="col">Value</th>
          <th scope="col">Purpose</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>padding</code></td>
          <td><code>var(--size-s) var(--size-m)</code></td>
          <td>Matches cell padding for visual alignment</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>text-align</code></td>
