    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Screen reader announcement:</strong> when a user navigates to a table, the caption is announced first, providing immediate context</li>
      <li><strong>Be descriptive:</strong> write captions that explain what data the table contains, not just "Table 1"</li>
      <li><strong>Include temporal context:</strong> if data is time-sensitive, include the relevant period</li>
      <li><strong>WCAG requirement:</strong> Success Criterion 1.3.1 requires data tables to be programmatically identifiable</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/table/"><code>&lt;table&gt;</code></a> - parent container (caption must be its first child)</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/thead/"><code>&lt;thead&gt;</code></a> - header group that follows the caption</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/figcaption/"><code>&lt;figcaption&gt;</code></a> - similar purpose for figures and images (compare: <code>&lt;caption&gt;</code> is for tables, <code>&lt;figcaption&gt;</code> is for figures)</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/summary/"><code>&lt;summary&gt;</code></a> - similar "label" role for <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> disclosure widgets</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
